  "prompt": "I had crush on my classmate, we used to talk a lot. But now we hardly talk to each other. Should I tell him that I loved him?",
  "response": "Deciding whether to express your feelings can be a tough choice, especially if your relationship has changed. Here are a few things to consider:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**: Determine if your feelings are still strong and if they are something you want to express.\n\n2. **Consider the Current Dynamic**: Think about why your communication has decreased. Are there circumstances that might affect how he would respond to your confession?\n\n3. **Gauge His Interest**: Try to assess whether he might feel the same way. Look for signs that he may still have an interest in being close.\n\n4. **Choose the Right Moment**: If you decide to share your feelings, find a comfortable and private time to talk, where both of you feel at ease.\n\n5. **Be Prepared for Any Outcome**: Understand that he may or may not feel the same way. It\u2019s important to be ready for any response and maintain respect for each other regardless of the outcome.\n\nUltimately, being honest about your feelings can lead to clarity, whether it brings you closer or helps you move on. Listen to your intuition as you make your decision.",
